column18:
Though records of actual national government spending at the level of month to month government expenditure on specific items are not available, there are datasets regarding total national government expenditure on specific sectors. The following are the links to the dataset: 

(1) Yearly data can be obtained from the national data portal: http://data.stats.gov.cn/workspace/index?m=hgnd Data can be downloaded as machine-readable spreadsheet (excel, CSV, etc.) but not open licensed; 

(2) Monthly reports on public spending including national and local expenditure, such as http://gks.mof.gov.cn/zhengfuxinxi/tongjishuju/201406/t20140611_1097509.html. But the data is not machine-readable or open licensed.

The Ministry of Environmental Protection data centre publishes hourly and daily data on air quality of cities (AQI, air quality level, and primary pollutant: http://datacenter.mep.gov.cn/report/air_daily/airDairyCityHour.jsp; http://datacenter.mep.gov.cn/report/air_daily/air_dairy_aqi.jsp. The data is listed on the website as tables but not downloadable. The dataset is not open licensed;

The Ministry of Environmental Protection data centre publishes weekly, monthly, quarterly, and yearly data on surface water quality (water temperature, pH, turbidity, dissolved oxygen, conductivity, permanganate index, ammonia nitrogen and total organic carbon): http://datacenter.mep.gov.cn/report/getCountGraph.do?type=waterHomePage. The data is listed on the website as tables but not downloadable. The dataset is not open licensed;

Yearly national environmental data can also be obtained on the national data portal: http://data.stats.gov.cn/workspace/index?m=hgnd. Data includes pollutant emissions in air and water. The dataset can be downloaded as machine-readable spreadsheet (excel, CSV, etc.) but not open licensed.

